HEADWORD: Decemvirate
<hw>De*cem"vi*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>decemviratus</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The office or term of
office of the decemvirs in Rome.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A body of ten men in authority.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decemvirship</ent>⟦br⟧
